      "user": "lise",
      "slug": "chaos-cinema-shaky-cam-staccato-editing",
      "title": "Chaos Cinema: Shaky Cam & Staccato Editing",
      "desc": "I have to take a long break from shaky cam films and films that use staccato editing. Unfortunately I'm at the point where it is ruining all films for me, even those where the methods are used effectively (as in The Hurt Locker). If I take a break from those films I may be able to watch one once in a while in the future without walking out.\n\nI need your help. Please list films that use either or both of these techniques so that I may avoid them during my break. I've listed the ones I know about.\n\nYou can see a video essay on these techniques called Chaos Cinema by Matthias Stork: Part 1: vimeo.com/28016047 and Part 2: vimeo.com/28016704",
